    "extras": [
      "Knutsford Express is the easiest long-distance option for most visitors, while route taxis with red plates are cheaper but tighter on baggage space and comfort.",
      "Domestic flights inside Jamaica are mostly charter-based rather than frequent scheduled hops, so treat them as premium time-savers between Kingston and Montego Bay instead of a default plan.",
      "Carry small Jamaican-dollar notes for beaches, route taxis, and small-entry sites even though many tourism businesses will quote or accept USD.",
      "Blue Lagoon boat rides, Rio Grande rafting, and Bob Marley Museum slots are worth booking ahead in peak season because daily capacity is limited.",
      "Road times can stretch after dark or in rain, especially on the Portland side, so keep east-coast transfer days light and avoid stacking major sightseeing after arrival."
